Package algorithms

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BubbleSort
    The most simple and less efficient (as being a senseful solution) of the sorting algorithms.
    HeapSort
    Heapsort is a in-place comparison-based sorting algorithm.
    InsertionSort
    The Insertion sort is a simple sorting algorithm that makes the ordered list by sorting one item at a time.
    IntroSort
    Introsort is a very efficient hybrid algorithm that uses both heapsort and quicksort.
    Main
    This is the class used for testing the algorithms' efficiency.
    MergeSort
    Merge sort is an O(n log n) relatively efficient comparison-based sorting algorithm.
    QuickSort
    Quicksort is an efficient sorting algorithm, being a comparison sort and using the "divide and conquer" principle.
    SelectionSort
    Selection sort is a sorting algorithm of in-place comparison sort by type.
